<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-03-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-03-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="374" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dudley</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-03-18"><hi rend="italic">March 18,
                                1901</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Dudley reports that the Peruvian Government has offered 3,000 soles
                            in settlement of the claim of Fowks, with the proviso that such action
                            is not citable as a precedent; that he considers the offer equitable,
                            and that the claimant is anxious to accept it.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>